# 1. Linux File Structure and Navigation

### Linux File System Hierarchy

/
|-- bin    → Essential command binaries  ==> /usr/bin     (symbolic link)
|-- boot   → Boot loader files
|-- dev    → Device files
|-- etc    → Configuration files
|-- home   → User home directories
|   ├── user1  → Home directory for user1
|   └── user2  → Home directory for user2
|-- lib    → Shared libraries            ==> /usr/lib     (symbolic link)
|-- lib64  → 64-bit shared libraries     ==> /usr/lib64   (symbolic link)
|-- root   → Root user home directory
|-- sbin   → System binaries             ==> /usr/sbin    (symbolic link)
|-- tmp    → Temporary files
|-- usr    → User programs and data
│   ├── bin    → User command binaries
│   ├── sbin   → User system binaries
│   ├── lib    → Libraries
│   └── share  → Architecture-independent data
|-- var    → Variable data files
│   ├── log    → System log files
│   ├── spool  → Mail, print queues
│   └── cache  → Application cache
|-- proc   → Process information (virtual)
|-- sys    → System files (virtual)


