### Cron Job Format
# ┌───────────── minute (0 - 59)
# │ ┌───────────── hour (0 - 23)
# │ │ ┌───────────── day of the month (1 - 31)  
# │ │ │ ┌───────────── month (1 - 12)
# │ │ │ │ ┌───────────── day of the week (0 - 6 Sunday to Saturday; 7 is also Sunday on some systems)
# │ │ │ │ │                                       
# │ │ │ │ │
# * * * * * command to be executed
### Example Cron Job
# 0 2 * * * /usr/bin/backup.sh            # run backup.sh every day at 2:00 AM
# 30 1 * * 1 /usr/bin/cleanup.sh          # run cleanup.sh every Monday at 1:30 AM
# */15 * * * * /usr/bin/check_updates.sh  # run check_updates.sh every 15 minutes

